leadership_approach|process_results_vision_people|concentrated|process|results|vision|people|Process-first leadership|This leadership pattern makes leadership reliable by giving the work structure, sequence, and repeatable standards. Results strengthens it by clarifying outcomes, ownership, and next steps, while Vision and People add range when the work needs longer-range direction or deeper trust and shared confidence.|The trap is organising the work beyond the point where movement, direction, or confidence is ready to build. Results, Vision, and People need deliberate attention when Process has set the pace but the work still needs clearer outcomes and next steps, longer-range direction, or deeper trust and shared confidence.|Lead with the structure and the way of working, then check whether the work needs clearer outcomes and next steps, longer-range direction, or deeper trust and shared confidence before the pattern narrows.|This is leadership that creates steadiness by making the work easier to coordinate and repeat. It works best when structure is balanced with enough movement, direction, and confidence for others to follow.|active|leadership_approach::process_results_vision_people::concentrated
