leadership_approach|people_results_process_vision|graduated|people|results|process|vision|A People-led leadership sequence|This leadership pattern starts with People and builds leadership around trust, communication, and shared confidence. Results strengthens the sequence by clarifying outcomes, ownership, and next steps, while Process and Vision add range as the work develops.|The trap is settling the work through People and Results before the later signals have shaped the response. Process and Vision need deliberate attention when the first route starts to crowd out stronger structure and coordination or longer-range direction.|Follow the sequence from People to Results, then bring in Process and Vision before the first route sets the whole answer.|This is leadership that moves in a clear order, starting with People before drawing on Results, Process, and Vision. It works best when trust is balanced with the later range before the response becomes fixed.|active|leadership_approach::people_results_process_vision::graduated
leadership_approach|people_results_process_vision|balanced|people|results|process|vision|Flexible People-led leadership|This leadership pattern gives your leadership several usable routes, led first by People. Results strengthens it by clarifying outcomes, ownership, and next steps, while Process and Vision add range when the priority shifts.|The trap is switching between leadership routes without naming the current priority. Results, Process, and Vision need deliberate attention so flexibility becomes a clear choice rather than mixed signals.|Name the current leadership priority, then choose whether the work needs deeper trust and shared confidence, clearer outcomes and next steps, stronger structure and coordination, or longer-range direction.|This is leadership that has access to People, Results, Process, and Vision without relying on one route alone. It works best when the current priority is named clearly enough for others to follow.|active|leadership_approach::people_results_process_vision::balanced
